    affiliation: "Politecnico di Milano"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  Evaluation protocol, harness, availability-timed (release-lag aligned)
  feature datasets, and reference
  baselines for multi-source next-day stock prediction (55 US large-caps,
  2015-2023; price, news, social, macro, inter-stock graphs). The committed
  result files regenerate every reference number with no download; the
  repository also documents from-scratch re-runs and two reproducibility
  audits that price individual protocol conditions (test-set model selection;
  non-temporal split leakage). Licensing: code MIT; derived feature tables
  CC-BY-4.0 with per-source terms preserved (the Cboe VIX close is
  redistributed as a cited extract under FRED citation-required terms) --
  see LICENSE and DATA-STATEMENTS.md.
keywords:
  - evaluation protocol
  - benchmark
  - data leakage
  - financial machine learning
  - reproducibility

# This artifact reproduces two published third-party baselines for an
# evaluation-methodology audit. They are NOT the work of the authors of this
# artifact; cite the originals below.
